lead_paragraph: The Labor Department said initial claims for state benefits declined 8,000 to 252,000 for the week ended Sept. 17.

headline.print_headline: Fall in Weekly Jobless Claims Raises Odds of Rate Increase
headline.main: Weekly Jobless Claims Fall, Raising Odds of Fed Rate Increase

snippet: The Labor Department said initial claims for state benefits declined 8,000 to 252,000 for the week ended Sept. 17....
abstract: Labor Dept reports initial claims for state unemployment benefits declined 8,000 to seasonally adjusted 252,000 for week; National Assn of Realtors says existing home sales fell in August because dearth of properties is keeping prices high.
